      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRINCESS ARNA (7) has looked good in winning her two starts since switching from Victoria to the Donny Smith yard. Led in scoring at this circuit and distance two back before cruising home last time at Redcliffe. Draws wider but is going well enough to overcome that and land the hat trick. MULLUM DOC (1) has been racing well of late. Led from wider when winning here four back and has placed twice since. Should be prominent from the ace draw. AMILLIONCHANCES (8) was midfield in a higher-graded race last week and had recorded a win and a close second in his previous two outings at this circuit and distance. Draws for a trail so can be competitive. GRACENAVA (2) should not have any excuses from the favourable draw having come from tougher barriers to win twice within her last three outings.",
